[
  "div",
  {
    "className": "content-wrapper"
  },
  [
    "h1",
    {},
    "The Articles"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    [
      "In Greek, almost every noun is preceded by an ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "article"
      ],
      ". The article tells us the gender, number, and case of the noun. There are two types: ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "Definite"
      ],
      " (\"the\") and ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "Indefinite"
      ],
      " (\"a/an\")."
    ]
  ],
  [
    "h2",
    {},
    "1. The Definite Article (Το Οριστικό Άρθρο)"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    "This is used when referring to a specific item. In English, we only have \"the\", but in Greek, it changes based on gender."
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "table-container"
    },
    [
      "table",
      {},
      [
        "thead",
        {},
        [
          "tr",
          {},
          [
            "th",
            {},
            "Gender"
          ],
          [
            "th",
            {},
            "Singular (The)"
          ],
          [
            "th",
            {},
            "Plural (The)"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "tbody",
        {},
        [
          "tr",
          {},
